and aryepiglottic folds.  Identify the laryngeal inlet, bordered by the epiglottis and the superior margin of the aryepiglottic fold on each side. The laryngeal inlet is the border between the laryngopharynx and the larynx.
On the prosection of the larynx with vessels, LOCATE the epiglottis
cadaver head, IDENTIFY the aryepiglottic fold, the piriform fossa lateral to it, the true and false vocal folds and the ventricle.

Locate the false vocal cords (vestibular folds) and the true vocal cords (vocal folds) and the ventricles. The space between the 2 vocal folds is referred to as the rima     glottidis. The space from the laryngeal inlet to the true vocal cords is called the vestibule and it includes the vestibular folds and the ventricles.  Inferior to the true vocal cords lies the infraglottic space.
